			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Instruments and Gear<a name="60309"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 5:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>What Velvett is saying is that item mods (including your epic mod) will not stack with your instrument mod.  
<br />

<br />
Your epic is a worn item with a modifier of 1.8.  If you equip your Thunderous Drum, an instrument with a modifier of 2.8, only the highest modifier will take effect.  In this example, your drum is higher so your percussion mod is 2.8.  The epic is simply a way to have a modifier for all instruments at once and a weapon at the same time.  The price you pay for that option is a lower modification than your instruments would provide.
<br />

<br />
Calli</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=287552">Muse Calliopeia the Bardess</a><br>
