			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Instruments and Gear<a name="60311"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 6:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Thats right.. anything with an instrument mod or a singing mod will not stack.. highest mod is what you get.
<br />

<br />
There are 3 seeming exceptions to this rule (or one, depending how you look at it).  These have to do with your singing skill... Amp, Resonance, and Harmonize.
<br />

<br />
Each of these ADD to your singing mod, rather than replacing it, so they DO stack with the item mod for singing.  
<br />

<br />
Now Amp is a song so it may not belong here.. There is no item involved.
<br />

<br />
Resonance is a clicky effect from the Voice of the Serpent adds +0.6 to whatever your singing mod is.
<br />

<br />
Harmonize is similar to Resonance, but it comes from the shadowsong cloak and adds +0.9</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
